<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way to think about insurance underwriting =
is that you build your underwriting model by:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Making a list of=C2=A0observable fact=
ors that are correlated with the risk you are insuring, and then</li>=09<li=
 style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Crossing off the factors=C2=A0that regulator=
s and politicians would get mad at you for using.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The first part helps you figure out the right =
price to charge for insurance, and requires some statistical sense. The sec=
ond part keeps you out of trouble, and requires some=C2=A0political sense. =
If your research discovers that people who drive red cars get in more car a=
ccidents than people who drive gray cars, sure, charge the red-car drivers =
more.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-7" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: =
transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a>=C2=A0If your research discovers that Jewish people get in more car acc=
idents than Christians, you=C2=A0put that research straight in the trash ca=
n! Why did you even do that research? What were you thinking? What is wrong=
 with you?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/29993996.261528/aHR0cHM6Ly9mb3J0dW5lLmNvbS93ZWxsLzIwMjIvMTIvMTMv=
Y292aWQtdW52YWNjaW5hdGVkLWdyZWF0ZXItcmlzay1jYXItY3Jhc2gtdHJhZmZpYy1hY2NpZGV=
udC1uZXctc3R1ZHktc2F5cy1jYW5hZGEtZ292ZXJubWVudC1yZWNvcmRzLXBmaXplci1tb2Rlcm=
5hLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc18bead2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Anyway</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you passed on getting the COVID vaccine, yo=
u might be a lot more likely to get into a car crash. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">During the summer of 2021, Canadian researcher=
s =E2=80=A6 found that the unvaccinated people were 72% more likely to be i=
nvolved in a severe traffic crash=E2=80=94in which at least one person was =
transported to the hospital=E2=80=94than those who were vaccinated. That=E2=
=80=99s similar to the increased risk of car crashes for people with sleep =
apnea, though only about half that of people who abuse alcohol, researchers=
 found. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The authors theorize that people who resist pu=
blic health recommendations might also =E2=80=9Cneglect basic road safety g=
uidelines.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The findings are significant enough that prima=
ry care doctors should consider counseling unvaccinated patients on traffic=
 safety=E2=80=94and insurance companies might base changes to insurance pol=
icies on vaccination data, the authors suggest.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am quite certain that, at least in the US, n=
o auto insurer is going to start asking drivers about their Covid vaccinati=
on status so that it can charge unvaccinated people more! Imagine the congr=
essional hearings!=C2=A0</p>
